This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: $1,500 cash bond is ordered to cover warrants in Burnett County cases 22CF51 and 22CF106.  Only judge may quash this warrant unless the cash bond is posted in full.

9:15 AM Cases 22CF51 and 22CF106 called together.  Defendant Ian Lee Magnuson not in court.  Attorney Eugene D Harrington in court for Ian Lee Magnuson.  Prosecuting attorney Kevin Thomas Schmidt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Def fails to appear, has $1k posted and history of FTA.  State requests warrant, forfeiture of cash.  Atty Harrington requests to stay the warrant for 2 weeks.  Court orders warrant, forfeiture of cash bond posted.  $1500 additional cash, only judge may quash.
Status conference on September 15, 2022 at 09:00 am.

4:13 PM Cases 22CF51 and 22CF106 called together.  Prosecuting attorney James Jay Rennicke Esq in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Ian Lee Magnuson in court.  Attorney Eugene D Harrington in court for Ian Lee Magnuson.  Both cases proceed to Waiver of Preliminary Hearing: Court informs def of rights to PH; waived by def.  Court finds waiver of right to PH knowingly, freely, voluntarily made.  Court finds factual basis for bind over.  State files Informations mirroring complaints. Cases on for Arraignment.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, def. waives reading.  Court informs def. of charges, possible penalties and rights.  NG plea entered to all counts.
Status conference scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Preliminary hearing on June 13, 2022 at 03:45 pm.
